WEBVTT

00:24.991 --> 00:26.392
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS: Moving vans
and boxes.

00:26.493 --> 00:27.793
Packing and unpacking.

00:27.894 --> 00:30.996
That's pretty much been my life
for as long as I can remember.

00:31.097 --> 00:33.265
My name is Davis Pell.

00:33.366 --> 00:36.301
Because of my mom's job,
we've had to move around a lot.

00:36.403 --> 00:39.104
I only just moved to America
from Australia.

00:39.205 --> 00:40.339
When you're always
the new kid,

00:40.440 --> 00:42.074
it's pretty hard
to make friends.

00:42.175 --> 00:46.211
Most of the time,
it's just me hanging by myself.

00:46.312 --> 00:48.380
Never having a chance to settle
down can be a bit lonely,

00:48.481 --> 00:51.617
but I've found ways
to keep things--

00:51.718 --> 00:52.451
- MAN: Uh-aw!

00:52.552 --> 00:53.585
- DAVIS: --interesting.

00:53.686 --> 00:54.953
Couldn't be.

00:55.055 --> 00:56.321
- MAN: Oh-ah!

00:59.659 --> 01:02.561
- ♪

01:19.646 --> 01:20.746
- Ah!

01:20.847 --> 01:24.116
- Oooh!

01:24.217 --> 01:26.518
- Rayzon, you followed me
to America?

01:26.619 --> 01:28.320
- I would go anywhere
to finally destroy you,

01:28.421 --> 01:30.456
Davis Pell.

01:30.557 --> 01:32.124
Even suburban Seattle.

01:32.225 --> 01:34.927
- Let's end this.

01:54.180 --> 01:55.347
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS:
It's possible

01:55.448 --> 01:59.051
I'm not the coolest guy
in the world.

01:59.152 --> 02:03.422
In fact, most people would say
I'm kind of a dork.

02:03.523 --> 02:04.656
And you know what?

02:04.757 --> 02:05.524
Uh!

02:05.625 --> 02:07.126
They might have a point.

02:07.227 --> 02:08.994
I mean, look at this.

02:09.095 --> 02:12.397
I'm having an imaginary fight,
and I'm losing.

02:13.967 --> 02:16.068
But not anymore.

02:16.169 --> 02:17.369
I'm at a new school.

02:17.470 --> 02:19.371
Heck, I'm in a new country.

02:19.472 --> 02:23.175
Things this year
will be different.

02:23.276 --> 02:24.610
I'm going to have friendS.

02:24.711 --> 02:26.111
I'm gonna be popular.

02:26.212 --> 02:28.914
Maybe I'll even get
a girlfriend for once.

02:29.015 --> 02:30.182
Whatever it takes.

02:30.283 --> 02:32.284
Starting this year,

02:32.385 --> 02:36.755
Davis Pell isn't
going to be a loser anymore.

02:36.856 --> 02:39.892
Uh!

02:44.063 --> 02:45.564
- I think you got 'em.

02:50.570 --> 02:52.704
- You didn't see
all of that, did you?

02:52.805 --> 02:54.406
- I think I can safely say

02:54.507 --> 02:59.811
I didn't see much as you
and Rayzon did.

02:59.913 --> 03:02.581
Rayzon.

03:02.682 --> 03:03.415
- Yeah.

03:03.516 --> 03:06.552
- Yeah.

03:06.653 --> 03:09.454
So...you live next door?

03:09.556 --> 03:12.558
- No, just a big fan
of porch swings.

03:12.659 --> 03:17.296
Travelling the country
porch swing to porch swing.

03:17.397 --> 03:19.498
- I hope
that works out for you.

03:19.599 --> 03:21.700
- Wait!

03:21.801 --> 03:25.003
Don't move!

03:25.104 --> 03:26.538
Shhhw.

03:29.876 --> 03:34.680
There was one behind you.

03:34.781 --> 03:35.914
- Thanks, Katniss.

03:36.015 --> 03:37.482
- No charge.

03:46.226 --> 03:49.528
- Hey, I was wondering.

03:49.629 --> 03:52.130
Maybe because I'm new in town
and all that,

03:52.232 --> 03:53.365
that maybe you could--

03:53.466 --> 03:57.436
- Uh, uh, uh, turn it around,
ninja warrior.

03:57.537 --> 04:00.472
I don't date boys
who play make-believe.

04:04.277 --> 04:05.744
- Right, got it.

04:15.888 --> 04:19.423
You're probably wondering
about the kaleidoscopes.

04:19.524 --> 04:20.959
My mom gets me one
every time we move.

04:23.062 --> 04:25.564
Told you we moved a lot.

04:25.665 --> 04:28.433
I've been collecting them
since I was a kid.

04:28.534 --> 04:30.535
I don't know
what it is about them.

04:30.637 --> 04:32.404
I guess I just like having
something to show

04:32.505 --> 04:34.273
for all the places
that I've lived.

04:37.243 --> 04:39.478
You also might have noticed
that sometimes

04:39.579 --> 04:42.114
I like to imagine stuff the way
I'd want it to be

04:42.215 --> 04:43.849
instead of how it really is.

04:43.950 --> 04:46.818
You know, like daydreaming.

04:46.919 --> 04:48.387
Let's just say that my daydreams

04:48.488 --> 04:51.823
are little more colorful
than most.

04:51.924 --> 04:54.393
- ♪

05:05.305 --> 05:06.104
- Hi, honey.

05:06.205 --> 05:08.073
- Hey, mom.

05:08.174 --> 05:10.642
- Are you excited to meet all
your new classmates tomorrow?

05:10.743 --> 05:12.311
- Excited?

05:12.412 --> 05:14.946
Um, have we met before?

05:17.016 --> 05:20.252
I'm sure you could have
plenty of mates if you tried.

05:20.353 --> 05:21.386
- Yeah.

05:21.487 --> 05:23.622
Let me guess,
if I just be myself.

05:23.723 --> 05:26.191
- Oh, honey,
it's high school.

05:26.292 --> 05:29.561
Nobody's really themselves yet.

05:29.662 --> 05:31.229
- Mm.

05:31.331 --> 05:34.666
- Things will look brighter
in the morning.

05:34.767 --> 05:36.568
- ♪

05:46.279 --> 05:47.946
- Yeah, you're right.

05:48.047 --> 05:49.614
Things do look much brighter.

05:53.252 --> 05:54.586
Here's your lunch.

05:57.924 --> 05:58.924
- Weird health food?

05:59.025 --> 06:01.660
- With all your allergies, yes.

06:01.761 --> 06:05.964
Oh, and...

06:06.065 --> 06:06.865
Ta-da!

06:08.034 --> 06:09.067
- Your lucky
first day sweater.

06:09.168 --> 06:12.070
- No, mom,
I thought you burned that.

06:12.171 --> 06:13.238
- You've worn it

06:13.339 --> 06:14.840
on your first day
for the last five years.

06:14.941 --> 06:17.476
- And every year
has been a complete disaster.

06:17.577 --> 06:19.778
It kind of defeats the purpose
of having a lucky sweater,

06:19.879 --> 06:20.746
now doesn't it?

06:20.847 --> 06:22.314
It's horrible,
and it's too small, ma.

06:22.415 --> 06:23.115
I can't wear it.

06:23.216 --> 06:24.282
- No, it's not.

06:24.384 --> 06:27.386
It's perfect.

06:27.487 --> 06:29.020
Your grandmother made it.

06:29.122 --> 06:31.089
- And Nana is legally blind.

06:31.190 --> 06:33.759
Mom, okay, I'm not wearing it.

06:41.067 --> 06:42.901
I'm not.

06:43.002 --> 06:46.471
- ♪

06:52.044 --> 06:53.011
- Can I help you?

06:53.112 --> 06:54.980
- I'm supposed
to get a schedule.

06:55.081 --> 06:56.615
- I'll pull it up for you.

07:00.853 --> 07:03.021
- Hi, everyone,
I'm Caitlyn Crisp,

07:03.122 --> 07:06.425
reminding you that Forksley High
is recycle friendly.

07:06.526 --> 07:08.059
We can save the planet.

07:08.161 --> 07:09.795
We only have one Earth,
you guys.

07:09.896 --> 07:12.431
So let's all pitch in
and treat it right.

07:12.532 --> 07:15.667
The Earth likes you,
and I like you, too.

07:15.768 --> 07:18.837
- ♪

07:26.112 --> 07:27.813
- What's that?

07:27.914 --> 07:29.448
- Your schedule.

07:29.549 --> 07:31.450
You just asked for it.

07:35.221 --> 07:37.255
- Thank you.

07:49.268 --> 07:51.303
- Pull it together, Davis.

07:51.404 --> 07:52.971
You can do this.

07:57.210 --> 07:58.543
Sorry, Nana.

08:05.284 --> 08:06.051
- CAITLYN: Hi, everyone.

08:06.152 --> 08:07.052
It's Caitlyn Crisp again.

08:07.153 --> 08:09.154
And on this edition
of "Caitlyn's World,"

08:09.255 --> 08:10.121
I'll be talking about

08:10.223 --> 08:11.890
the hottest event
of the season--

08:11.991 --> 08:14.960
this fall's Sweetheart Dance
at Forksley High.

08:15.061 --> 08:18.997
You don't want
to miss a minute of it.

08:20.266 --> 08:23.134
That last blog that you posted
on your site was amazing.

08:23.236 --> 08:24.369
- I know.

08:24.470 --> 08:27.772
And I love that people
love my videos.

08:27.874 --> 08:31.309
But still, I can't help but feel
like there's something missing.

08:31.410 --> 08:32.577
- What do you mean?

08:32.678 --> 08:34.446
- People in this school
look to me

08:34.547 --> 08:36.014
to make their life
more fulfilling.

08:36.115 --> 08:38.482
And I just keep giving them
more of the same.

08:38.583 --> 08:40.452
There's got to be something new.

08:44.056 --> 08:46.291
- I want adventure.

08:46.392 --> 08:47.125
- Uh!

08:47.226 --> 08:48.360
- Excitement.

08:51.464 --> 08:53.365
- Maybe even danger.

08:57.303 --> 08:59.604
Ugh!

08:59.705 --> 09:02.541
- ♪

09:07.580 --> 09:09.281
- DAVIS: Okay.

09:09.382 --> 09:11.650
Let's do this.

09:11.751 --> 09:13.084
- CAITLYN: I don't
know what it is.

09:13.185 --> 09:15.186
But I do know one thing.

09:15.288 --> 09:17.923
It's out there waiting for me.

09:48.588 --> 09:51.089
- Who are you?

09:51.190 --> 09:52.357
- I'm new.

09:52.458 --> 09:55.093
- Oh, the new guy.

09:55.194 --> 09:57.696
You care to introduce yourself
to the rest of the class?

09:57.797 --> 09:59.431
- No.

09:59.532 --> 10:02.167
- Good, take a seat.

10:02.268 --> 10:05.770
- ♪

10:36.102 --> 10:39.037
- ♪

10:42.241 --> 10:44.342
- Here, let me help.

10:52.551 --> 10:54.185
- Thanks.

10:54.286 --> 10:55.453
- Cool accent.

10:55.554 --> 10:56.955
Is it real?

10:57.056 --> 10:59.190
- Why would I fake an accent?

10:59.291 --> 11:01.359
- To sound cool.

11:01.460 --> 11:03.161
- You think I sound cool?

11:05.331 --> 11:10.035
- See you around.

11:10.136 --> 11:12.037
There's definitely something
interesting about him.

11:12.138 --> 11:13.705
- GIRL: Love the accent.

12:15.401 --> 12:17.068
- How did you do that?

12:17.169 --> 12:20.004
- Do what?

12:20.106 --> 12:21.106
- Hey.

12:21.207 --> 12:22.607
Who are you?

12:22.708 --> 12:26.911
- I--I--see ya.

12:29.548 --> 12:31.382
- Who was that guy?

12:31.484 --> 12:33.418
- I don't know.

12:47.066 --> 12:49.000
- CAITLYN: How did he get
all the way down there?

12:55.775 --> 12:57.075
- A vampire?

12:57.176 --> 12:58.009
- I'm telling you.

12:58.110 --> 13:00.145
He didn't have a reflection.

13:00.246 --> 13:02.247
I didn't see it
with my own eyes.

13:02.348 --> 13:05.083
He could be exactly
what I'm looking for.

13:05.184 --> 13:06.885
- What about Bon?

13:06.986 --> 13:10.421
- The Bon's
a little bit simple.

13:11.490 --> 13:13.224
Not you, Bon, another Bon.

13:21.834 --> 13:24.035
He's so mysterious.

13:24.136 --> 13:28.473
- Look at him
trying to eat human food.

13:28.574 --> 13:31.976
- ALL: Aw.

13:33.345 --> 13:34.746
I have an idea.

13:37.683 --> 13:40.318
- Bon, does that pizza
have garlic in it?

13:40.419 --> 13:42.153
- Yeah.

13:42.254 --> 13:44.823
- Perfect.

13:44.924 --> 13:48.026
I saw you weren't
enjoying your food.

13:48.127 --> 13:51.362
You should have this instead.

13:51.463 --> 13:54.065
- Wow, that's really nice
of you and all,

13:54.166 --> 13:56.434
but I--I can't
actually eat that.

13:56.535 --> 13:57.402
I'm allergic.

13:57.503 --> 13:59.037
- To the garlic?

13:59.138 --> 14:02.874
- Uh, well...yeah,
and the cheese

14:02.975 --> 14:05.276
and the yeast and--

14:05.377 --> 14:07.278
basically the whole pizza.

14:07.379 --> 14:10.682
- Yeah, but one little bite
can't hurt.

14:10.783 --> 14:13.151
- Yeah, I mean, one bite
can't hurt that much.

14:13.252 --> 14:15.520
I mean, how allergic
can I really be?

14:15.621 --> 14:17.255
- Mm-hmm.

14:27.833 --> 14:30.101
- Uh...it was delicious.

14:30.202 --> 14:31.269
Thanks.

14:46.018 --> 14:48.519
- No, I don't like it.

14:48.621 --> 14:49.687
- What, Bon?

14:49.788 --> 14:51.723
- The poster, I don't like.

14:51.824 --> 14:55.126
- Uh, yeah,
I don't like it either.

14:55.227 --> 14:56.961
- Well, I guess you guys
don't need me here for this.

14:57.062 --> 14:58.596
I'm just gonna head out.

14:59.932 --> 15:00.832
- We should take it down.

15:00.933 --> 15:01.866
- Yeah.

15:01.967 --> 15:05.203
- Wait, wait, guys.

15:05.304 --> 15:06.604
We can talk about this, right?

15:06.705 --> 15:08.139
We can talk about this, please.

15:08.240 --> 15:10.308
- Did you see how he reacted
to the garlic?

15:10.409 --> 15:11.276
- Everybody saw!

15:13.112 --> 15:15.513
What happened
to Bon and the guys?

15:16.916 --> 15:19.317
Oh, no!

15:39.972 --> 15:42.073
- Oh my gosh.

15:42.174 --> 15:44.509
- O-M-G, he's sparkling.

15:44.610 --> 15:47.779
Pics or it didn't happen.

15:51.650 --> 15:52.450
- You have to send that to me.

15:55.754 --> 15:59.257
- Oh my gosh.

15:59.358 --> 16:01.125
- Wow.

16:11.036 --> 16:12.870
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS: Oh, please.

16:12.972 --> 16:14.339
Kill me now.

16:14.440 --> 16:16.040
- Come with me.

16:21.280 --> 16:22.714
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS: Looks like
I'm gonna get my wish.

16:22.815 --> 16:24.082
She does plan on killing me.

16:24.183 --> 16:26.084
Probably leave my body
in the woods.

16:26.185 --> 16:28.886
- Do you feel
like you can be honest with me?

16:28.988 --> 16:30.989
- Uh...sure.

16:31.090 --> 16:34.058
- You're pale
and you dress strangely.

16:34.159 --> 16:35.927
- Oh, you're starting
with the honesty.

16:36.028 --> 16:38.429
- Tell me what you are.

16:38.530 --> 16:40.365
- What do you mean?

16:40.466 --> 16:42.166
- You're awkward.

16:42.267 --> 16:44.836
You really don't say anything
interesting.

16:44.937 --> 16:48.873
- Oh, you should be
a motivational speaker.

16:48.974 --> 16:52.477
- But I find myself
drawn to you.

16:54.713 --> 16:55.813
- What was that?

16:55.914 --> 16:57.148
- You don't have a reflection
in the mirror.

16:57.249 --> 16:58.282
You can't eat normal food.

16:58.384 --> 17:00.618
And you sparkle
in direct sunlight.

17:00.719 --> 17:02.253
- I sparkle?

17:07.092 --> 17:08.693
I'm sparkling.

17:08.794 --> 17:09.594
- Say it.

17:09.694 --> 17:10.494
- Say what?

17:10.596 --> 17:11.762
- I know what you are.

17:11.864 --> 17:12.630
- You do?

17:12.731 --> 17:13.765
- Yes, I do.

17:13.866 --> 17:16.067
Say it out loud.

17:16.167 --> 17:20.271
- Uh, I--I--I'm pale.

17:20.372 --> 17:22.240
No reflection.

17:22.340 --> 17:27.211
Uh, sparkling...like a vampire.

17:27.311 --> 17:27.811
- Uh!

17:27.913 --> 17:29.447
It's true?

17:35.287 --> 17:35.787
- Sure.

17:37.089 --> 17:38.322
Please promise to meet me
by the first tree

17:38.424 --> 17:40.625
at the school entrance
at 8:30 tomorrow.

17:40.726 --> 17:41.526
- Okay.

17:47.633 --> 17:50.301
Oh, boy.

17:50.402 --> 17:51.702
I'm dead.

18:14.993 --> 18:17.261
You look so cool.

18:17.362 --> 18:19.864
- Thanks.

18:19.965 --> 18:21.199
- Let's go in.

18:21.300 --> 18:23.434
- We just walk in
like in front of everyone?

18:23.535 --> 18:24.569
- Mm-hmm.

18:24.670 --> 18:26.170
Come on.

18:37.349 --> 18:39.016
- CAITLYN: Oh, hi, Bon.

18:39.118 --> 18:40.985
- BON: No way.

18:56.135 --> 18:57.635
- Is it true?

18:57.736 --> 18:59.270
- Is it true?

19:04.977 --> 19:06.544
What do you think?

19:11.350 --> 19:13.885
- This is totally
the most amazing thing

19:13.986 --> 19:16.154
to ever happen at this cool.

19:16.255 --> 19:21.425
It's true, Davis Pell
is a really, actually...

19:21.527 --> 19:23.161
a vampire.

19:32.137 --> 19:33.337
- Psst.

19:36.942 --> 19:38.843
Does this happen to you a lot?

19:38.944 --> 19:40.111
Do you go to new schools
and people think

19:40.212 --> 19:43.014
you're a supernatural creature?

19:43.115 --> 19:47.285
Oh, were you Rocky Raccoon
at your last school?

19:47.386 --> 19:51.289
- What makes you think
I'm not really a vampire?

19:51.390 --> 19:54.292
- You act like you're 14,
not 400.

19:54.393 --> 19:57.461
You go out during the day,
which pretty much goes against

19:57.563 --> 19:59.864
the most basic tenant
of vampire lure.

19:59.965 --> 20:03.201
And you are in no way suave.

20:03.302 --> 20:05.703
Oh, yeah,
and vampires aren't real.

20:19.084 --> 20:23.387
Don't worry,
I'm not going to say anything.

20:23.488 --> 20:24.589
- Why not?

20:24.690 --> 20:27.658
- Because you're making
everybody look like idiots.

20:27.759 --> 20:30.127
I kind of love that.

20:30.229 --> 20:32.396
But some advice.

20:32.497 --> 20:33.898
You're going
to have to step up your game

20:33.999 --> 20:36.400
if you want to keep this up.

20:36.501 --> 20:39.303
- ♪

21:03.695 --> 21:05.162
- Ah!

21:13.839 --> 21:15.273
Ha!

21:24.816 --> 21:26.450
This isn't working.

21:29.755 --> 21:30.488
Wah, wah, ha, ha!

21:30.589 --> 21:32.356
Ugh, no, no.

21:32.457 --> 21:36.294
- ♪

21:49.574 --> 21:50.374
- Hey, Vi.

21:50.475 --> 21:51.542
Thanks for helping me out
with this.

21:51.643 --> 21:52.710
You know, I've been up all night
trying to figure

21:53.945 --> 21:56.180
- Well, I decided if you're
going to make a mockery

21:56.281 --> 21:59.250
of my school's social order,
then I want in.

21:59.351 --> 22:00.818
And you definitely need my help.

22:00.919 --> 22:02.086
- That's true.

22:02.187 --> 22:04.789
- Now, I'm going
to get you looking the part,

22:04.890 --> 22:07.258
but you've got to get yourself
sounding the part.

22:07.359 --> 22:10.528
Talk to me
like you're really a vampire.

22:10.629 --> 22:12.663
- Okay.

22:12.764 --> 22:16.567
I'm totally a vampire.

22:16.668 --> 22:19.070
- What was that?

22:19.171 --> 22:21.472
- It was a vampire.

22:21.573 --> 22:24.141
- For someone
who already has an accent,

22:24.242 --> 22:26.410
you're terrible at accents.

22:26.511 --> 22:29.347
- Okay, well, first off,
I'm not the one with an accent.

22:29.448 --> 22:30.848
You are.
- Oh.

22:30.949 --> 22:34.151
- And secondly,
just tell me how I should sound.

22:34.252 --> 22:35.753
- Okay.

22:35.854 --> 22:39.256
The modern vampire
is more of a cross between

22:39.358 --> 22:41.926
a constipated model
and a freshman poetry major.

22:42.027 --> 22:42.893
- What?

22:42.994 --> 22:45.096
- Okay, repeat after me.

22:45.197 --> 22:46.864
You wouldn't understand.

22:50.068 --> 22:51.402
- You wouldn't understand.

22:51.503 --> 22:53.304
- More like you don't want
to deal with anything.

22:53.405 --> 22:54.405
- Should it really be
this much work

22:54.506 --> 22:55.973
to seem like I don't care?

22:56.074 --> 22:57.942
- For you, yes.

23:04.149 --> 23:06.117
- Thanks for helping me
pick out all these clothes.

23:06.218 --> 23:08.219
- No charge, Edward Cullen.

23:09.421 --> 23:11.188
Okay, how's
the vampire voice coming?

23:11.289 --> 23:11.922
- Oh.

23:13.125 --> 23:14.859
You wouldn't understand.

23:15.827 --> 23:16.761
Not bad.

23:16.862 --> 23:18.629
- Yeah?

23:18.730 --> 23:20.231
So what else is there to know
about vampires?

23:20.332 --> 23:21.599
Like I know
all the regular stuff

23:21.700 --> 23:25.236
like wooden stakes and sunlight
and all that stuff.

23:25.337 --> 23:27.438
But what else?

23:27.539 --> 23:29.507
- There's a couple things.

23:29.608 --> 23:33.544
For instance, vampires
are terrified of rabbits.

23:33.645 --> 23:36.347
They're incapable
of singing "Happy Birthday."

23:36.448 --> 23:38.582
Oh, and this is
an important one.

23:38.683 --> 23:41.419
If you beat a vampire
in a staring contest,

23:41.520 --> 23:43.654
it renders them powerless.

23:43.755 --> 23:45.756
- A staring contest?
- Mm-hmm.

23:45.857 --> 23:47.224
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

23:47.325 --> 23:48.492
- I don't believe you.

23:48.593 --> 23:50.761
- Fine, you don't
have to believe me.

23:50.862 --> 23:52.496
Here's proof.

24:06.745 --> 24:07.645
- Doh!

24:07.746 --> 24:08.245
Okay!

24:09.381 --> 24:10.748
- Okay, you win.

24:10.849 --> 24:13.184
But seriously, we really
need to figure a way

24:13.285 --> 24:15.052
we can sell this at school.

24:15.153 --> 24:16.987
- Don't worry.

24:17.088 --> 24:19.190
I have a few ideas.

24:19.291 --> 24:21.625
Now you got the hair
and the clothes.

24:21.726 --> 24:24.061
Okay, let's start
with the basics.

24:24.162 --> 24:26.630
Wear these at all times.

24:26.731 --> 24:28.799
- ♪

24:33.004 --> 24:35.806
- Perfect.

24:38.343 --> 24:39.310
- He showed me his fangs.

24:40.378 --> 24:41.712
- GIRL: It's just
like Edward.

24:41.813 --> 24:42.613
- Oops.

24:42.714 --> 24:45.883
- GIRL: Oh my gosh,
he's so cute.

24:45.984 --> 24:48.786
- Okay, vampires' eyes
are always changing colors.

24:48.887 --> 24:52.223
So you're going to need
to wear these contact lenses.

24:52.324 --> 24:52.923
- GIRL: There he is.

24:53.024 --> 24:55.125
Turn around.

24:55.227 --> 24:56.060
Look at his eyes.

24:59.931 --> 25:02.700
- ♪

25:02.801 --> 25:04.602
- And on this edition
of "Caitlyn's World,"

25:04.703 --> 25:09.406
Forksley High's
very own bloodsucker Davis Pell.

25:09.508 --> 25:10.908
- VI: Some vampires can fly.

25:11.009 --> 25:12.810
So we've got to get you
off the ground.

25:12.911 --> 25:13.978
- Look!

25:14.079 --> 25:17.848
- ♪

25:17.949 --> 25:19.483
- Oh, yeah.

25:20.886 --> 25:21.852
- There's no way.

25:21.953 --> 25:24.855
- ♪

25:40.372 --> 25:42.206
- How did he do that?

25:42.307 --> 25:46.911
- ♪

25:47.012 --> 25:48.178
- CAITLYN: Today
on "Caitlyn's World,"

25:48.280 --> 25:51.181
I have a story you can
really sink your teeth into.

25:51.283 --> 25:54.151
Davis Pell,
undead and loving it.

25:54.252 --> 25:56.120
How old are you?

25:57.856 --> 26:01.992
Time...is for those
waiting to die.

26:02.093 --> 26:03.594
- So true.

26:03.695 --> 26:05.062
So true.

26:05.163 --> 26:09.033
And this week's winner of
the smile contest is Davis Pell.

26:09.134 --> 26:12.836
Thanks to all my new followers
for logging on to vote.

26:12.938 --> 26:15.706
Looking towards the future,
will you be attending

26:15.807 --> 26:20.911
Forksley High's annual
Sweetheart Dance?

26:21.012 --> 26:23.781
- If you'll be my date.

26:23.882 --> 26:24.782
- Of course.

