- ♪

26:35.193 --> 26:36.560
♪ So get your game on ♪

26:36.661 --> 26:38.195
♪ Get, get your game on ♪

26:38.296 --> 26:41.932
♪

26:54.713 --> 26:56.413
♪ So get your game on ♪

26:56.514 --> 26:58.515
♪ Get, get your game on ♪♪

26:58.617 --> 27:00.117
- This guy comes
into our school,

27:00.218 --> 27:03.787
steals are girls, our friends,
our pizza slices.

27:03.888 --> 27:04.688
Why?

27:04.789 --> 27:06.357
Because he's a vampire.

27:06.458 --> 27:07.424
Well, I'm a quarterback.

27:07.525 --> 27:08.425
And I was here first.

27:08.526 --> 27:09.226
- Yeah!

27:09.327 --> 27:10.227
Let's go, baby!

27:10.328 --> 27:11.962
Whoo!

27:15.800 --> 27:18.669
- I was more complaining.

27:18.770 --> 27:21.505
It wasn't really anything
to get excited about.

27:21.606 --> 27:24.375
- You were using
your huddle voice.

27:24.476 --> 27:25.676
- Is that what I sound like?

27:25.777 --> 27:27.611
- Hey, I have an idea.

27:27.712 --> 27:30.414
I have this uncle
who's way into vampires.

27:30.515 --> 27:31.382
He can maybe help us.

27:31.483 --> 27:32.216
- Call him.

27:32.317 --> 27:33.651
- Okay.

27:34.753 --> 27:36.987
But I have to warn you.

27:37.088 --> 27:37.888
He's a little weird.

27:37.989 --> 27:39.523
- Call him!

27:47.432 --> 27:49.133
- Hello?

27:49.234 --> 27:50.501
- BOY: Uncle Derrick?

27:50.602 --> 27:52.603
- Oh?

27:52.704 --> 27:58.042
- Is this...Baron Von Awesome?

28:00.979 --> 28:05.015
If what you're saying is true,
and I have been noticing

28:05.116 --> 28:09.153
a number of signs indicating
just such an occurrence,

28:09.254 --> 28:14.825
I will stalk the monster
and I will kill it.

28:14.926 --> 28:16.660
- How do we know you can do it?

28:16.761 --> 28:18.495
What's your story?

28:18.596 --> 28:21.031
- My story?

28:27.138 --> 28:30.574
I was born in a graveyard
at midnight.

28:30.675 --> 28:31.975
- Whoa.

28:32.077 --> 28:35.546
- And still an infant,
I was abandoned.

28:35.647 --> 28:38.982
I found myself nursing
from a mother emu.

28:39.084 --> 28:42.786
She took me in, and her family
raised me as her own.

28:42.887 --> 28:45.355
They taught me how to hunt.

28:45.457 --> 28:46.957
And how to kill.

28:47.058 --> 28:50.094
- What does any of this
have to do with vampires?

28:50.195 --> 28:53.530
- My skills are vast,
I assure you.

28:53.631 --> 28:56.834
I have the yellow belt in nine
different forms of "ka-ra-tay,"

28:56.935 --> 29:00.537
which technically makes me
a third degree black belt.

29:00.638 --> 29:02.072
And I've defeated
the game Castlevania,

29:03.241 --> 29:07.544
And I have seen the movie
"Van Helsing" 47 times!

29:07.645 --> 29:09.246
And I hated that movie.

29:09.347 --> 29:10.848
- That--that's all great,

29:10.949 --> 29:12.649
but how is it going to help you
get this guy?

29:15.086 --> 29:16.754
Mark my words.

29:16.855 --> 29:19.423
I will hunt this creature down
to the ends of the world.

29:19.524 --> 29:21.825
There is nowhere he can hide.

29:21.926 --> 29:25.362
- Finding him
won't be a problem.

29:25.463 --> 29:26.930
- Excellent.

29:34.839 --> 29:36.840
- Which one is he?

29:36.941 --> 29:40.244
- He's right there.

29:40.345 --> 29:42.446
- Excellent.

29:42.547 --> 29:44.014
- So, what's your plan?

29:44.115 --> 29:46.316
- This container
is filled with water

29:46.417 --> 29:49.787
caught from the base
of the Carpathian Mountains.

29:49.888 --> 29:52.890
It is renowned for
its vampire-killing properties.

29:52.991 --> 29:56.593
When I spill it on him,
it's going to be poof...

29:56.694 --> 29:58.629
goodbye, vampire boy!

30:01.766 --> 30:03.167
- Sssh, sssh, sh, sh.

30:03.268 --> 30:04.768
Sssh.

30:11.176 --> 30:12.209
Hello!

30:15.380 --> 30:16.213
- Can I help you?

30:16.314 --> 30:17.014
- Yeah.

30:17.115 --> 30:19.883
I am the water delivery person.

30:19.984 --> 30:23.420
And I'm here
to deliver the water.

30:23.521 --> 30:24.555
- TEACHER: No water here.

30:24.656 --> 30:27.558
You probably want
the teacher's lounge.

30:27.659 --> 30:32.963
- Or perhaps--or perhaps
it was right here!

30:34.065 --> 30:37.467
- Ah!

30:37.569 --> 30:38.869
Evil creature!

30:42.507 --> 30:47.644
Drink this up you nasty,
smelly thing from beyond!

30:47.745 --> 30:52.983
terror.

31:02.327 --> 31:03.126
Yeah.

31:09.300 --> 31:10.400
- Mm.

31:10.501 --> 31:11.768
I guess we're gonna need a mop.

31:14.505 --> 31:16.707
- Hey, Vi.

31:16.808 --> 31:20.177
- So, this is what
your lair looks like.

31:20.278 --> 31:23.447
I expected more candelabras
and flowy curtains.

31:23.548 --> 31:25.249
- Ha, ha, very funny.

31:27.285 --> 31:31.655
- So...how do I look?

31:31.756 --> 31:35.225
- Not to feed your already
rapidly growing ego,

31:35.326 --> 31:38.629
but you do look relatively
presentable tonight.

31:38.730 --> 31:40.364
- You're so sweet.

31:40.465 --> 31:41.231
- Mmm.

31:44.202 --> 31:48.605
So...what's with
all the telescopes?

31:48.706 --> 31:52.442
- They're kaleidoscopes.

31:52.543 --> 31:54.378
- Why do you have all of them?

31:54.479 --> 31:57.881
- Oh, well, my mom gets me one
every time we move.

31:57.982 --> 32:00.450
- Wow, you do move a lot.

32:01.953 --> 32:06.723
Yeah, I know it's weird, but it
makes my mom happy, so...

32:06.824 --> 32:12.396
and actually,
I--I kind of like them, too.

32:15.500 --> 32:17.000
They're pretty much
the only things I really have

32:17.101 --> 32:18.902
from all the places
that I've lived.

32:26.244 --> 32:28.679
- I don't think
they're weird at all.

32:28.780 --> 32:30.080
I like them.

32:30.181 --> 32:33.317
They're cool.

32:33.418 --> 32:34.918
- Thanks.

32:41.192 --> 32:41.992
- So...

32:45.129 --> 32:47.731
You got your dancing shoes on?

32:47.832 --> 32:51.401
- I don't know
about that one.

32:51.502 --> 32:53.737
- Oh, of course.

32:53.838 --> 32:55.072
Get over here.

32:55.173 --> 32:56.073
- What? Why?

32:56.174 --> 32:59.076
- I'm going to teach you
how to slow dance.

32:59.177 --> 33:02.646
- What makes you
think that I--?

33:02.747 --> 33:03.914
Okay.

33:04.015 --> 33:05.515
I don't know how to slow dance.

33:06.884 --> 33:08.452
Okay, so you're going
to put your hands there.

33:08.553 --> 33:09.386
- Yeah.

33:09.487 --> 33:10.954
- And I'll put my hands there.

33:11.055 --> 33:13.423
You rock back and forth.

33:13.524 --> 33:15.125
You can start to spin.

33:15.226 --> 33:17.995
- Okay.

33:18.096 --> 33:20.764
- And you can occasionally
look at the girl.

33:20.865 --> 33:22.199
Yeah.

33:22.300 --> 33:25.769
- Yeah.

33:25.870 --> 33:28.505
Am--am I doing it right?

33:28.606 --> 33:29.940
- Yeah.

33:30.041 --> 33:32.909
- ♪

33:37.415 --> 33:39.182
- MOM: Davis,
your girlfriend's here.

33:51.763 --> 33:54.331
- Bye.

33:54.432 --> 33:56.233
- Hey.

33:56.334 --> 33:59.069
You should come
to the dance tonight.

33:59.170 --> 34:01.905
- Definitely not my scene.

34:02.006 --> 34:05.876
- There's a good chance
I might make a fool of myself.

34:05.977 --> 34:08.545
- Slightly more tempting.

34:10.715 --> 34:12.081
- But alas,
I don't have anything

34:12.183 --> 34:17.187
quite darling enough
to wear to such an occasion.

34:17.288 --> 34:19.389
- Well, I'm sure you'd look good
in anything you wore.

34:25.630 --> 34:27.496
Anyways, see ya.

34:33.603 --> 34:34.404
- CAITLYN: You look great.

34:34.505 --> 34:35.405
- DAVIS: Thanks.

34:35.505 --> 34:39.543
You, too.

34:44.581 --> 34:48.385
- ♪

34:55.426 --> 34:56.893
- Let's go sit down.

35:02.166 --> 35:05.235
- ♪

35:10.007 --> 35:14.644
- You are the most beautiful
girl I have ever seen.

35:14.745 --> 35:16.580
- In all your lives?

35:16.681 --> 35:18.648
- Yes.

35:18.749 --> 35:20.584
In every single one of 'em.

35:24.589 --> 35:25.489
- That's not fair.

35:25.590 --> 35:26.223
That's my girl.

35:26.324 --> 35:27.190
- Okay.

35:27.291 --> 35:28.892
You know I am
the head cheerleader.

35:28.993 --> 35:30.360
- Quiet, Not Caitlyn.

35:30.461 --> 35:33.463
- Ugh!

35:33.564 --> 35:34.431
- Hey, hey.

35:34.532 --> 35:35.565
Check it out.

35:37.368 --> 35:38.468
Hello.

35:44.642 --> 35:45.842
- Oh, hey.

35:45.943 --> 35:47.110
Have you see Davis?

35:47.211 --> 35:48.311
- No.

35:48.412 --> 35:50.814
- Hello, everyone, can I have
your attention, please?

35:50.915 --> 35:54.251
It is now time to announce
the Sweetheart Couple.

35:54.352 --> 35:56.920
Now there were a lot of
really cute couples this year.

35:57.021 --> 35:59.823
But unfortunately,
there can only be one.

35:59.924 --> 36:04.761
This year's
Mr. and Miss Sweetheart are...

36:04.862 --> 36:07.330
Caitlyn Crisp and Davis Pell!

36:43.935 --> 36:46.303
- And now
for the spotlight dance.

36:48.272 --> 36:51.508
- ♪

37:14.332 --> 37:16.166
- Ooh, my gosh,
I love this song!

37:16.267 --> 37:18.335
I have to go get the girls.

37:18.436 --> 37:22.973
- ♪

37:23.074 --> 37:26.610
♪ Buckle up
and hold on tight ♪

37:26.711 --> 37:32.782
♪ All abroad on this
endless ride to forever ♪

37:32.883 --> 37:38.221
♪ Until forever ♪

37:38.322 --> 37:41.625
♪ Every night I feel so alive ♪

37:41.726 --> 37:44.694
♪ These are the signs
of the endless night ♪

37:44.795 --> 37:48.031
♪ Forever ♪

37:48.132 --> 37:50.800
♪ Until forever ♪

37:50.901 --> 37:53.503
♪

38:17.061 --> 38:19.162
- Why aren't you
doing anything?

38:19.263 --> 38:20.997
- This guy is a clever one.

38:21.098 --> 38:22.432
My plan is to study him

38:22.533 --> 38:23.433
and then destroy him!

38:23.534 --> 38:25.769
- Oh, you are so fired!

38:25.870 --> 38:30.573
- ♪

38:30.675 --> 38:33.643
♪ Forever ♪

38:33.744 --> 38:36.313
♪ Until forever ♪

38:36.414 --> 38:37.981
♪ And ever ♪

38:38.082 --> 38:40.350
♪ And ever ♪

38:40.451 --> 38:46.089
♪♪

39:14.118 --> 39:15.652
- CAITLYN: Tonight
was so much fun.

39:15.753 --> 39:18.755
- Yeah, it was the best.

39:18.856 --> 39:22.459
Caitlyn, there's something
I need to talk to you about.

39:22.560 --> 39:23.560
- Oh, no, not tonight.

39:23.661 --> 39:25.261
Uh, I'm exhausted.

39:25.363 --> 39:26.896
Let's talk about it tomorrow,
okay?

39:26.997 --> 39:29.499
- No, no, no.

39:29.600 --> 39:30.734
It's important.

39:30.835 --> 39:32.736
And I've been meaning to tell
you this for a while now,

39:32.837 --> 39:35.071
I just didn't know how.

39:35.172 --> 39:36.539
- You want to make
our relationship official?

39:36.640 --> 39:37.407
- No.

39:37.508 --> 39:41.010
No, I mean, yes, of course I do.

39:41.112 --> 39:41.878
It's just that--

39:41.979 --> 39:42.879
- No, no, no, no.

39:42.980 --> 39:44.080
I'm too excited.

39:44.181 --> 39:45.415
I have to go tell the girls.

39:46.851 --> 39:48.885
Come over to my house on Friday,
and we'll go over everything,

39:48.986 --> 39:51.588
okay?

39:51.689 --> 39:52.389
- Yeah.

39:52.490 --> 39:53.690
Okay, great.

40:10.241 --> 40:11.107
- GIRL: Do you really think
that Caitlyn's

40:11.208 --> 40:12.542
going to go through with it?

40:12.643 --> 40:13.710
- Why wouldn't she?

40:13.811 --> 40:14.711
Wouldn't you?

40:15.846 --> 40:19.382
It's like the coolest
thing to happen to anyone.

40:19.483 --> 40:23.086
- I can't believe Davis Pell
is going to turn Caitlyn Crisp

40:23.187 --> 40:25.221
into a vampire.

40:25.322 --> 40:27.090
I'm so jealous.

40:33.631 --> 40:35.265
- Caitlyn is telling everybody
that you're going to turn her

40:35.366 --> 40:36.933
into a vampire on Friday.

40:37.034 --> 40:38.168
- What?

40:38.269 --> 40:39.836
Oh, come on, she can't
actually believe that.

40:39.937 --> 40:42.672
- Uh, you're talking about
the girl that already believes

40:42.773 --> 40:44.607
you're a real-life vampire.

40:44.708 --> 40:47.644
She's expecting you
to bite her on the neck

40:47.745 --> 40:49.746
and turn her into a vampire.

40:49.847 --> 40:50.914
You can't let this go on.

40:51.015 --> 40:51.948
It's too far.

40:52.049 --> 40:53.082
- I tried to tell her.

40:53.184 --> 40:56.186
- But you didn't.

40:56.287 --> 40:58.354
- I thought we were having fun.

40:58.456 --> 41:02.892
- Davis, you're the only one
who's having fun anymore.

41:02.993 --> 41:04.594
- Oh, I see now.

41:04.695 --> 41:05.895
You're jealous.

41:07.131 --> 41:08.631
You think I'm jealous
of Caitlyn?

41:08.732 --> 41:09.732
- No.

41:09.834 --> 41:12.335
I think you're jealous of me
for being popular.

41:12.436 --> 41:16.105
Why would you be jealous
of Caitlyn?

41:16.207 --> 41:18.208
- No reason.

41:18.309 --> 41:20.243
No reason at all.

41:20.344 --> 41:22.412
Have a great time Friday night.

41:32.156 --> 41:35.558
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS:
Okay, here we go.

41:36.861 --> 41:38.228
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS: I don't
know what I'm worrying about.

41:38.329 --> 41:39.863
I mean, she likes me, right?

41:39.964 --> 41:41.431
I can just confess,

41:41.532 --> 41:43.466
and we can put
all of this behind us.

41:48.739 --> 41:50.340
Hey, Caitlyn.

41:50.441 --> 41:53.643
I've got something
to confess to you.

41:53.744 --> 41:57.313
I'm not really a vampire.

41:57.414 --> 41:58.748
- Oh, Davis.

41:58.849 --> 42:00.517
I don't care about that.

42:00.618 --> 42:02.485
I like you for you.

42:02.586 --> 42:04.120
Now kiss me.

42:11.128 --> 42:13.429
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS: Come on,
Davis, hold it together.

42:13.531 --> 42:16.165
Just tell her the truth,
and everything will be fine.

42:16.267 --> 42:18.001
Besides, she can't really think

42:18.102 --> 42:19.636
I'm going to turn her
into a vampire.

42:24.608 --> 42:26.109
Uh-oh.

42:36.353 --> 42:38.922
It looks like
you've got a nice place here.

42:39.023 --> 42:40.757
If I could
actually see anything.

42:40.858 --> 42:42.458
- Come.

42:42.560 --> 42:44.327
- Caitlyn,
there's--there's something

42:44.428 --> 42:46.563
I've been meaning to tell you.

43:09.086 --> 43:11.721
- Bite me.

43:11.822 --> 43:14.357
- Uh, well...you see,

43:14.458 --> 43:16.192
there's something
that I really need to tell you.

43:16.293 --> 43:18.895
- Ssh, don't spoil the moment
with your talking.

43:18.996 --> 43:20.363
Just do it.

43:23.033 --> 43:24.500
- Okay.

43:31.875 --> 43:36.746
Ugh, Caitlyn, there's
a whole bunch of people here.

43:38.749 --> 43:39.882
- Mm-hmm.

43:39.984 --> 43:41.551
Better not disappoint.

43:49.994 --> 43:51.961
- I have to pee.

44:19.423 --> 44:20.256
- Ready?

44:21.458 --> 44:22.659
- Mm-mm.

44:35.372 --> 44:38.141
- How does it feel?

44:38.242 --> 44:40.943
- It doesn't really
feel like anything.

44:41.045 --> 44:43.079
- Uh, that's how
it's supposed to feel.

44:43.180 --> 44:44.380
That means it's working.

44:44.481 --> 44:47.216
That means it's working!

44:47.317 --> 44:50.053
- GIRL: You didn't
even bite her.

44:50.154 --> 44:52.021
- He can't turn her.

44:52.122 --> 44:53.790
- May--maybe
it just didn't take.

44:53.891 --> 44:54.557
I'll try again.

44:54.658 --> 44:55.692
Let me try again.

45:06.103 --> 45:07.637
- It's ketchup.

45:07.738 --> 45:08.638
I knew it.

45:08.739 --> 45:10.840
He's a liar!

45:10.941 --> 45:12.709
He's a faker!

45:12.810 --> 45:14.277
- DAVIS: Dude,
it was just a joke.

45:14.378 --> 45:16.979
Guys, it's just me Davis.

45:17.081 --> 45:18.948
It's just me Davis, guys.

45:19.049 --> 45:20.316
It's just me Davis.

45:20.417 --> 45:22.018
Guys, I was joking.

45:22.119 --> 45:23.119
It was a joke.

45:23.220 --> 45:24.120
We can talk about this, right?

45:24.221 --> 45:27.123
Can't you take a joke?

45:29.293 --> 45:32.061
- I guess he
wasn't a vampire after all.

45:32.162 --> 45:33.830
Come on.

45:33.931 --> 45:36.833
- ♪

45:36.934 --> 45:40.002
- That is just what
he wants you to think.

45:40.104 --> 45:42.071
His time will come.

46:02.159 --> 46:03.760
- Hey, honey.

46:03.861 --> 46:04.293
- DAVIS:

46:04.394 --> 46:05.528
- You okay?

46:09.800 --> 46:11.534
- Yeah.

46:11.635 --> 46:14.370
I'm just gonna go to bed.

46:14.471 --> 46:15.304
- Are you sure
you're all right?

46:15.405 --> 46:18.841
- DAVIS: Yes, mom, I'm fine.

46:21.044 --> 46:24.147
I know it's tough on you
sometimes

46:24.248 --> 46:29.418
with all the moving
and the changes.

46:29.520 --> 46:33.156
I am sorry you have
to go through that all the time.

46:33.257 --> 46:34.624
- Okay.

46:34.725 --> 46:35.958
Thanks.

46:52.843 --> 46:53.743
- Do you know why

46:53.844 --> 46:57.747
I get you a kaleidoscope
every time we move?

46:57.848 --> 46:59.849
- Why, mom?

46:59.950 --> 47:03.986
- Because you look in it,
and it's beautiful.

47:06.757 --> 47:11.861
But the slightest
turn of the wheel...

47:11.962 --> 47:17.099
can change everything.

47:17.201 --> 47:20.102
Thing is, that change

47:20.204 --> 47:23.206
can be beautiful, too.

47:23.307 --> 47:24.841
Sometimes maybe
even more beautiful

47:24.942 --> 47:27.310
than it was before.

47:27.411 --> 47:30.246
- This change stinks.

47:30.347 --> 47:33.916
- I know.

47:34.017 --> 47:37.386
You know, with everything that's
happened since you arrived,

47:37.487 --> 47:40.323
I'm sure there's something here

47:40.424 --> 47:43.659
you think is beautiful.

47:43.760 --> 47:48.130
- ♪

48:17.895 --> 48:18.694
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS:
Have you ever really

48:18.795 --> 48:20.630
not wanted to go to school?

48:20.731 --> 48:24.133
Like you have a zit or a test
you didn't study for?

48:24.234 --> 48:26.669
- Loser!

48:26.770 --> 48:28.771
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS: This was
like all those times combined.

48:28.872 --> 48:29.805
- Liar!

48:29.907 --> 48:34.176
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS:
Times like 40 billion.

48:34.278 --> 48:35.645
- Jerk!

48:49.559 --> 48:51.327
- Okay, it sounds great.

48:51.428 --> 48:52.595
- Okay, stop it right there.

48:52.696 --> 48:54.497
Yeah, no, add that
to the second clip.

48:54.598 --> 48:55.932
- Like a vampire.

48:56.033 --> 48:56.866
- It's true?

48:56.967 --> 48:58.267
- Yeah.

48:58.368 --> 48:59.502
- CAITLYN: Play it back.

48:59.603 --> 49:01.504
Please promise to meet me by
the first tree--

49:01.605 --> 49:05.174
- Hey, Caitlyn.

49:05.275 --> 49:07.610
- What are you doing here?

49:07.711 --> 49:09.712
- I don't remember
there being any cameras there.

49:09.813 --> 49:11.514
What are you working on?

49:11.615 --> 49:13.249
- Nothing.

49:13.350 --> 49:14.817
It has nothing to do with you.

49:14.918 --> 49:16.252
- I'm not too sure that's true.

49:16.353 --> 49:17.153
- Would you just go?

49:17.254 --> 49:19.322
I can't even look at you.

49:20.724 --> 49:24.060
- DAVIS: Okay, I just--I just
wanted to tell you

49:24.161 --> 49:28.264
that what I did was wrong,
and I'm a complete goon.

49:28.365 --> 49:33.002
And...I'm sorry.

49:33.103 --> 49:37.773
- No, Davis,
I'm sorry...for you.

49:37.874 --> 49:40.042
You're a sad person,
and you should go.

49:45.382 --> 49:46.849
- Yeah.

49:53.457 --> 49:54.590
- CAITLYN: Get back to work.

49:54.691 --> 49:56.292
I'm gonna check my site.

49:56.393 --> 49:57.460
Oh my gosh!

49:57.561 --> 49:58.995
Ten thousand subscribers!

49:59.096 --> 49:59.996
I've gone national!

50:02.432 --> 50:04.233
- Oh, I just lost one.

50:22.252 --> 50:23.452
- Psst, hey.

50:23.553 --> 50:25.087
- What do you want?

50:25.188 --> 50:27.656
Need more footage of me
acting like a jerk?

50:27.758 --> 50:30.359
- No, I've got plenty of that.

50:30.460 --> 50:31.861
I want to give you something.

50:36.266 --> 50:37.199
- What is it?

50:37.300 --> 50:38.300
- Just watch.

50:38.402 --> 50:40.403
It'll help you, believe me.

50:40.504 --> 50:42.338
- Why are you helping me?

50:45.876 --> 50:49.078
I too know what it's like to try
to be someone you're not

50:49.179 --> 50:50.913
for a woman's affections.

50:51.014 --> 50:53.682
- For Rita?

50:53.784 --> 50:56.385
- I like her,
but I hate video cameras.

51:15.906 --> 51:17.273
- Cut.

51:17.941 --> 51:19.208
- BOY: Yeah, I got it.

51:19.309 --> 51:21.677
- You better have, because
I'm not doing it again.

51:21.778 --> 51:25.047
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS: Here it was,
the ugly truth.

51:25.148 --> 51:27.883
And no daydream
could ever cover it up.

51:27.984 --> 51:30.586
What I saw in that video
was so shocking,

51:30.687 --> 51:33.289
so mind blowing,
so life altering,

51:33.390 --> 51:36.692
if I ever hope to show my face
at that school again,

51:36.793 --> 51:39.628
I had to show everyone
what I had just seen.

51:39.729 --> 51:42.498
I had to fix everything.

51:42.599 --> 51:45.234
But how?

51:45.335 --> 51:48.137
- ♪

52:11.561 --> 52:13.929
- MAN: Whoo-ha-ha-ha!

52:14.030 --> 52:15.197
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS: I had
set a plan in motion

52:15.298 --> 52:16.832
for the Creepy Carnival.

52:16.933 --> 52:20.202
And I had
just the right costume.

52:20.303 --> 52:24.773
Actually, it was
my only costume.

52:24.875 --> 52:25.875
- Ooh.

52:25.976 --> 52:29.578
- DAS GH:
Now it was go time.

52:29.679 --> 52:31.580
But first things first.

52:31.681 --> 52:34.917
- ♪

52:41.892 --> 52:42.992
- Dracula?

52:43.093 --> 52:44.560
Really?

52:44.661 --> 52:46.562
- Don't be afraid.

52:46.663 --> 52:49.765
I'm not actually a vampire.

52:49.866 --> 52:51.400
- I gotta get back
to the haunted house.

52:51.501 --> 52:53.102
- No, wait.

52:55.138 --> 52:57.439
I just wanted to tell you that

52:57.541 --> 52:59.542
when I started
doing all of this,

52:59.643 --> 53:02.778
all this pretending...

53:02.879 --> 53:04.346
I thought it'd be the only way

53:04.447 --> 53:06.982
that I'd finally
get some real friends.

53:07.083 --> 53:08.984
- I'd say you made plenty.

53:09.085 --> 53:12.021
- No.

53:12.122 --> 53:13.722
Just one.

53:27.237 --> 53:30.105
Here, I want you to have this.

53:41.551 --> 53:44.620
Anyways, I'll--I'll
talk to you later.

54:09.012 --> 54:13.048
"Sometimes I pretend things
are what they really aren't.

54:13.149 --> 54:15.951
"But with you,
I don't need to pretend.

54:16.052 --> 54:18.754
"You make real life way
better than make believe.

54:18.855 --> 54:20.589
Davis."

54:35.605 --> 54:36.739
- Hi, everyone.

54:36.840 --> 54:39.642
And welcome to Forksley High's
Creepy Carnival.

54:39.743 --> 54:40.976
Tonight, we'll be showing

54:41.077 --> 54:43.178
"The Revenge of the Creature
from the Black Lagoon."

54:46.650 --> 54:47.483
- What are you doing here?

54:50.120 --> 54:53.455
- Everyone, I've got something
to tell you.

54:53.556 --> 54:55.524
I have something to show you.

54:59.329 --> 55:01.163
- Liar!

55:01.264 --> 55:02.564
- Liar!

55:02.666 --> 55:03.966
- Loser!

55:04.067 --> 55:06.368
- Loser!

55:06.469 --> 55:08.837
Lame-o!

55:08.938 --> 55:13.008
Those are all names
that I deserve to be called.

55:13.109 --> 55:15.077
And those are just the Ls.

55:15.178 --> 55:19.648
I owe all of you
a sincere apology.

55:19.749 --> 55:22.618
Except for one person.

55:22.719 --> 55:24.353
Caitlyn Crisp.

55:25.789 --> 55:30.392
- Caitlyn Crisp has used and
lied to every single one of us.

55:30.493 --> 55:32.995
And I have proof.

55:33.096 --> 55:36.565
This is what Caitlyn Crisp
really is.

55:36.666 --> 55:39.368
- ♪

55:47.577 --> 55:50.112
- Okay, that's--that's
obviously not Caitlyn Crisp.

55:50.213 --> 55:53.816
That is the Creature
from the Black Lagoon.

55:53.917 --> 55:55.451
Looks pretty good.

55:55.552 --> 55:59.221
- I don't know what this
hurtful liar is trying to prove,

55:59.322 --> 56:01.824
but we can all agree
it's pathetic.

56:07.163 --> 56:07.863
- Cut.

56:07.964 --> 56:08.697
Did you get that?

56:08.798 --> 56:09.531
- BOY: Yeah, I got it.

56:09.632 --> 56:10.666
- Is that thing off?

56:10.767 --> 56:11.433
- BOY: I turned it off.

56:11.534 --> 56:13.402
- Good.

56:13.503 --> 56:16.171
You know, I just can't stop
thinking about all these idiots

56:16.272 --> 56:19.308
who actually believe
this vampire stuff is real.

56:19.409 --> 56:23.579
What a bunch of boosers
and followers.

56:23.680 --> 56:25.280
- What?

56:25.382 --> 56:28.550
- Are you helping Davis
take down Caitlyn?

56:28.651 --> 56:31.220
- Kinda.

56:31.321 --> 56:34.923
- I didn't think
you had it in you.

56:35.024 --> 56:36.258
- Of course all the students
at school are sheep

56:36.359 --> 56:37.893
who will do anything
I say anyway.

56:37.994 --> 56:40.195
Oh, no, no, no.

56:40.296 --> 56:43.632
Bon, stop him.

56:44.634 --> 56:45.501
- Wait.

56:45.602 --> 56:47.202
- It's Bon, again.

56:47.303 --> 56:48.003
Oh, no.

56:48.104 --> 56:49.037
When are you going to realize

56:49.139 --> 56:50.472
you're just
high-school arm candy?

56:50.573 --> 56:52.374
What an idiot.

56:52.475 --> 56:53.342
End call.

56:53.443 --> 56:54.643
Okay.

56:54.744 --> 56:55.944
Ah!

56:56.045 --> 56:59.982
- This is your beloved Caitlyn.

57:00.083 --> 57:02.151
She has made a fool
out of all of us.

57:02.252 --> 57:03.285
- CAITLYN: That's not true.

57:03.386 --> 57:04.319
The great thing

57:04.421 --> 57:05.954
about high school
being a popularity contest--

57:06.055 --> 57:07.890
the rules are
written by the winners.

57:07.991 --> 57:09.425
That's not what I meant.

57:09.526 --> 57:13.328
Oh, stop it!

57:13.430 --> 57:16.031
Agh!

57:25.909 --> 57:27.810
- I don't know how he did this.

57:27.911 --> 57:30.946
But you guys know I would never
say anything bad about you.

57:31.047 --> 57:35.184
You're all my friends,
and I adore you.

57:53.269 --> 57:54.470
- Hey, guys.

57:54.571 --> 57:55.170
Guys!

57:55.271 --> 57:55.804
Listen!

57:55.905 --> 57:57.272
Hey, listen!

58:02.679 --> 58:06.381
- This is high school, okay?

58:06.483 --> 58:10.586
No one really knows
who they are yet.

58:10.687 --> 58:14.423
And we're all still
trying to figure things out.

58:14.524 --> 58:19.461
I mean, you guys hated me
like two minutes ago.

58:19.562 --> 58:21.897
And I don't blame you.

58:21.998 --> 58:24.166
Because I pretended
to be something I wasn't

58:24.267 --> 58:30.405
so that you would like me,
and I'm so sorry.

58:30.507 --> 58:33.208
But take a look at yourselves
for a second.

58:33.309 --> 58:38.247
Is it any different for you?

58:38.348 --> 58:44.052
I mean, Caitlyn Crisp is no more
Miss Perfect than I am a--

58:44.153 --> 58:47.489
- Bloodsucker!

58:47.590 --> 58:52.060
- Look, that's
our water delivery guy.

58:52.161 --> 58:53.028
- Who are you?

58:53.129 --> 58:54.963
- I am your arch nemesis.

58:55.064 --> 58:57.032
- Okay.

58:57.133 --> 59:00.002
- I'm Baron Von Awesome,
a vampire hunter.

59:00.103 --> 59:02.037
- Dude, that's, uh,
Stewart's uncle.

59:02.138 --> 59:03.572
He still thinks
you're a vampire.

59:03.673 --> 59:04.840
He wants to kill you.

59:04.941 --> 59:06.575
- What?

59:06.676 --> 59:08.677
I think it's been
pretty well established

59:08.778 --> 59:11.847
that I'm not an actual vampire.

59:11.948 --> 59:13.715
I was getting
way meaningful down here.

59:15.485 --> 59:18.620
It is not wise to ignore me,
creature.

59:18.721 --> 59:22.524
Especially when...

59:22.625 --> 59:25.661
I have your girlfriend.

59:25.762 --> 59:26.828
- Vi!

59:29.599 --> 59:30.432
- Where does that door go?

59:30.533 --> 59:32.134
- Uh, the roof.

59:32.235 --> 59:34.303
- ♪

59:47.450 --> 59:49.851
- Come, demon, face your fate!

59:49.953 --> 59:51.153
- What are you talking about?

59:51.254 --> 59:52.921
There's no way
I could get up there.

59:53.022 --> 59:55.257
- Use your dragon wings.

59:55.358 --> 59:57.225
- This whole not really being
a vampire thing

59:57.327 --> 59:59.194
just isn't sticking with you,
is it?

59:59.295 --> 01:00:01.129
- Uh, enough of your treachery,
bloodsucker.

01:00:01.230 --> 01:00:05.434
I am coming down.

01:00:13.710 --> 01:00:15.877
- Bloodsucker!

01:00:15.979 --> 01:00:19.348
- I told you,
I'm not a vampire!

01:00:19.449 --> 01:00:22.651
- ♪

01:00:26.623 --> 01:00:29.625
- At last!

01:00:29.726 --> 01:00:30.926
Ah!

01:00:31.027 --> 01:00:33.295
With such speed and agility,

01:00:33.396 --> 01:00:36.665
how can you claim
to not be a vampire?

01:00:48.077 --> 01:00:49.444
- You got me.

01:00:50.847 --> 01:00:53.415
- I'm the real deal,
and I'm real dangerous.

01:00:53.516 --> 01:00:56.952
And right now, I'm real mad.

01:00:57.053 --> 01:01:00.656
So I'd advise you
not to challenge me.

01:01:00.757 --> 01:01:03.692
Give up now.

01:01:03.793 --> 01:01:04.726
- Arm yourself!

01:01:07.530 --> 01:01:08.797
- Okay.

01:01:20.476 --> 01:01:21.743
- Ah!

01:01:31.020 --> 01:01:31.853
Ah!

01:01:31.954 --> 01:01:33.255
- Wait, wait, wait, wait!

01:01:35.625 --> 01:01:38.293
Uh...

01:01:38.394 --> 01:01:41.229
this is pointless, slayer.

01:01:41.330 --> 01:01:43.165
You know that
there's only one way

01:01:43.266 --> 01:01:46.501
to render a vampire powerless.

01:01:46.602 --> 01:01:47.969
- Of course.

01:01:48.071 --> 01:01:50.505
A staring contest.

01:01:50.606 --> 01:01:52.474
- Exactly.

01:01:52.575 --> 01:01:54.276
And I accept your challenge.

01:02:02.151 --> 01:02:03.885
On the count of three.

01:02:03.986 --> 01:02:06.121
One, two--

01:02:12.061 --> 01:02:13.261
- Three!

01:03:01.511 --> 01:03:03.612
- You fought bravely, human.

01:03:09.652 --> 01:03:11.286
- I see.

01:03:11.387 --> 01:03:15.357
There's humanity,
even in the undead.

01:03:18.528 --> 01:03:20.395
I will spare your life.

01:03:20.496 --> 01:03:21.863
I will spare his life!

01:03:27.036 --> 01:03:29.538
- Uh, thanks.

01:03:29.639 --> 01:03:30.672
Vi!

01:03:30.773 --> 01:03:33.074
I forgot Vi!

01:03:33.176 --> 01:03:35.010
- Oh, move, out of the way!

01:03:39.849 --> 01:03:41.249
- Go get her, Dracula!

01:03:43.152 --> 01:03:45.720
- ♪

01:03:55.631 --> 01:03:56.898
- You just made the team.

01:04:05.241 --> 01:04:07.342
- Finally.

01:04:07.443 --> 01:04:09.744
- You're welcome.

01:04:09.846 --> 01:04:12.013
- So are you
going to untie me now?

01:04:12.114 --> 01:04:14.482
- Well, maybe.

01:04:14.584 --> 01:04:16.585
But I'm thinking you're probably
blaming me for all of this,

01:04:16.686 --> 01:04:18.320
and that you might
actually hit me.

01:04:18.421 --> 01:04:19.688
- That's true.

01:04:22.525 --> 01:04:24.926
- But I might also be grateful
that you saved me

01:04:25.027 --> 01:04:26.995
and give you that kiss
you've been looking for.

01:04:31.734 --> 01:04:33.568
- You don't need arms for that.

01:05:00.930 --> 01:05:02.697
- So cool.

01:05:02.798 --> 01:05:05.767
- I'm really sorry
for everything that I said.

01:05:05.868 --> 01:05:07.502
- Yeah.

01:05:10.273 --> 01:05:11.806
- Oh, oh, psychic.

01:05:21.617 --> 01:05:25.020
- So, we're like a couple now,
huh?

01:05:25.121 --> 01:05:26.454
- Yeah, don't get used to it.

01:05:26.555 --> 01:05:27.989
You're not even my type.

01:05:28.090 --> 01:05:30.025
- How's that?

01:05:30.126 --> 01:05:32.060
- Well, I'm more
into werewolves.

01:05:32.161 --> 01:05:36.798
- BOTH:

01:05:36.899 --> 01:05:41.269
- Oh, by the way.

01:05:41.370 --> 01:05:43.505
Thank you for the kaleidoscope.

01:05:43.606 --> 01:05:46.241
- You're welcome.

01:05:46.342 --> 01:05:49.945
- ♪

01:05:55.685 --> 01:05:59.387
- ♪

01:06:00.990 --> 01:06:03.191
- DAVIS: Oh, let me
show you how to dance.

01:06:03.292 --> 01:06:04.993
- VI: Now this is my scene.

01:06:05.094 --> 01:06:06.828
- ♪ Hold on tight ♪

01:06:06.929 --> 01:06:09.264
♪ All aboard
on this endless ride ♪

01:06:09.365 --> 01:06:10.632
- DAVIS'S THOUGHTS: So maybe

01:06:10.733 --> 01:06:12.934
I'm not the coolest guy
in the world, but who cares.

01:06:13.035 --> 01:06:15.470
I made some friends,
and I got the girl.

01:06:15.571 --> 01:06:17.539
The right girl.

01:06:17.640 --> 01:06:20.575
And they all seem
to like the real Davis.

01:06:20.676 --> 01:06:22.477
And you know what?

01:06:22.578 --> 01:06:24.279
That's pretty cool to me.

01:06:24.380 --> 01:06:25.347
- ♪ On and on ♪

01:06:25.448 --> 01:06:27.349
♪ It goes on and on ♪

01:06:27.450 --> 01:06:29.417
♪ It goes on and on ♪

